# 🚀 PRD — Space Park Fun World
**Product Requirements Document**
Version 1.0 | June 2026

---

## 1. Project Overview

| Field | Details |
|-------|---------|
| **Project Name** | Space Park Fun World |
| **Type** | 3D Open-World Theme Park Explorer |
| **Language** | Python |
| **Engine** | Ursina Engine (free, Python-native 3D engine) |
| **Platform** | Windows (Desktop) |
| **Target Audience** | General / All ages |
| **Tone & Style** | Colorful, cartoony, Disney-in-space aesthetic |

---

## 2. Vision Statement

> "A vibrant, open-world 3D space-themed amusement park where players freely explore colorful zones, play mini games for points, and experience the magic of a Disney-style park — but in outer space."

This is **not** a survival game. There are **no health bars, no missions, no danger**. It is a pure exploration and fun experience.

---

## 3. Engine Choice — Ursina Engine

**Why Ursina?**
- 100% Python — no C++ needed
- Free and open source
- Built-in 3D rendering, collision, entity system
- Smooth camera controls out of the box
- Easy to install: `pip install ursina`
- Supports textures, lighting, models, UI — everything needed
- Active community and documentation

---

## 4. Core Features

### 4.1 Open World Park
- Large, seamlessly explorable 3D space park
- No loading screens between areas
- Colorful, themed environment with glowing lights, space backdrops, alien plants, decorative rockets
- Floating platforms, space-age architecture, neon signage

### 4.2 Day / Night Cycle
- **Toggle Button**: Press **`N`** key to switch between Day and Night
- **Day Mode**: Bright, colorful park lighting with a distant sun, vivid colors
- **Night Mode**: Dark space sky filled with stars, neon park lights glow, atmospheric lighting
- Smooth transition animation between modes (gradual sky color shift over ~3 seconds)

### 4.3 Player Character
- Visible **astronaut character** in a space suit
- **Gender selection screen** at startup: Male or Female astronaut
- Male suit: White with blue visor
- Female suit: White with pink/purple visor
- Animated walking, idle, and interaction poses

### 4.4 Camera System
- **Smooth follow** third-person camera by default (orbits behind player)
- **Key `C`** → Toggle between **First Person** and **Third Person**
- Third Person: Camera floats 3 units behind and 2 units above the player, smoothly follows
- First Person: Camera locks to player head position, mouse look
- No rigid/rigorous camera snapping — all transitions are smooth and interpolated

### 4.5 Player Movement
| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `W / A / S / D` | Move forward / left / back / right |
| `Mouse` | Look around |
| `Space` | Jump |
| `Shift` | Run |
| `C` | Toggle First / Third Person camera |
| `N` | Toggle Day / Night |
| `E` | Interact (enter mini game, read sign) |
| `ESC` | Pause / Main Menu |

---

## 5. Park Layout & Zones

The park is divided into **3 main zones** with elements **mixed throughout**:

```
         ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
         │           🌌 SPACE PARK FUN WORLD        │
         │                                         │
         │   [ENTRY PLAZA]    [OBSERVATION DECK]   │
         │        ↓                                │
         │   [GALAXY GAMES ZONE]   [ALIEN MARKET]  │
         │        ↓                                │
         │   [COSMIC RIDES ZONE]                   │
         │        ↓                                │
         │   [ROCKET LAUNCHPAD]                    │
         └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Zone 1 — Entry Plaza
- Grand welcome gate with glowing "SPACE PARK FUN WORLD" sign
- Decorative fountain shooting glowing space liquid upward
- Park map sign (shows zones)
- Alien NPC characters wandering around (non-interactive, ambient)
- Colorful flags and banners
- Ticket booth (decorative)

### Zone 2 — Galaxy Games Zone
- Central hub for all 4 mini game stations
- Each station has a glowing arcade-style kiosk
- Scoreboard display near each station showing Top 5 high scores
- Carnival-style lighting and decorations

### Zone 3 — Cosmic Rides Zone
- **Roller Coaster**: Visible track wrapping around the zone (decorative, animated cars running on track)
- **Spinning Rocket Ride**: Rocket pods spinning around a central tower (animated, decorative)
- **Observation Deck**: Elevated platform at the edge of the park with panoramic view of space
- **Rocket Launchpad**: A large decorative rocket that periodically "launches" (particle effect + animation)

### Mixed Throughout the Park
- Alien NPC characters in various costumes walking paths
- Glowing alien plant decorations
- Food cart stands (decorative — hot dogs shaped like rockets, drinks in space helmets)
- Floating holographic signs pointing to attractions
- Ambient particle effects (glowing dust, floating stars)

---

## 6. Mini Games (4 Stations)

### 🎯 Mini Game 1 — Asteroid Shooting Gallery
- **Concept**: Asteroids float past on a conveyor path. Player aims and clicks to shoot them with a laser gun.
- **Duration**: 60 seconds per round
- **Scoring**:
  - Small asteroid: 10 pts
  - Medium asteroid: 25 pts
  - Large asteroid: 50 pts
  - Bonus multiplier for consecutive hits (x2 after 5 hits)
- **Controls**: Mouse aim + Left Click to shoot
- **Lives**: 3 misses allowed before round ends early
- **UI**: Timer bar, score counter, hit streak indicator

### 🐛 Mini Game 2 — Alien Whack-a-Mole
- **Concept**: Cute aliens pop up randomly from glowing holes in the floor. Player clicks on them before they hide.
- **Duration**: 45 seconds
- **Scoring**:
  - Green alien: 10 pts
  - Blue alien (fast): 25 pts
  - Gold alien (rare): 100 pts
  - Penalty: -15 pts for clicking the "friendly" purple alien (marked with a heart)
- **Controls**: Mouse aim + Left Click
- **Difficulty ramp**: Speed increases every 15 seconds
- **UI**: Timer, score, alien type legend

### 🌀 Mini Game 3 — Space Maze
- **Concept**: Navigate a 3D top-down or first-person maze to reach the exit rocket before time runs out.
- **Duration**: 90 seconds per attempt
- **Scoring**:
  - Finish the maze: 500 pts base
  - Time bonus: +10 pts per second remaining
  - Collect floating stars inside maze: +20 pts each
- **Controls**: `W/A/S/D` to navigate, `C` to toggle view
- **Features**: Glowing walls, rotating star collectibles, exit marked with a green beacon
- **Maze size**: Medium (not too large) — takes ~30-60 seconds to solve

### 🚀 Mini Game 4 — Rocket Race
- **Concept**: Pilot a small rocket through a course of floating rings in space. Pass through all rings as fast as possible.
- **Duration**: Race against the clock, not other players
- **Scoring**:
  - Base: 1000 pts minus time taken in seconds × 10
  - Bonus: +50 pts for each ring passed cleanly (center)
  - Penalty: -100 pts for hitting a ring wall
- **Controls**: `W/S` = thrust/brake, `A/D` = steer, mouse = look
- **Track**: A looping course of 20 rings through asteroid fields and space scenery
- **UI**: Speed gauge, ring counter, timer

---

## 7. Scoring & Leaderboard System

### Local Save
- All high scores saved to a local `scores.json` file in the game directory
- Persists between sessions

### Score Structure (per mini game)
```json
{
  "asteroid_shooting": [{"name": "Player1", "score": 1250, "date": "2026-06-08"}],
  "whack_a_mole":      [{"name": "Player1", "score": 870, "date": "2026-06-08"}],
  "space_maze":        [{"name": "Player1", "score": 720, "date": "2026-06-08"}],
  "rocket_race":       [{"name": "Player1", "score": 950, "date": "2026-06-08"}]
}
```

### Post-Game Score Screen
- Shows current score vs personal best
- Option to enter name (up to 12 characters)
- Top 5 leaderboard shown
- "Play Again" and "Return to Park" buttons

---

## 8. UI & HUD

### Main Menu (on launch)
- "SPACE PARK FUN WORLD" title with animated stars
- Character selection: Male / Female astronaut
- Enter Name input
- **Play** button
- **Scores** button (view all leaderboards)
- **Quit** button

### In-Park HUD (minimal, non-intrusive)
- Top-left: Current zone name
- Top-right: Day/Night toggle button icon + `[N]` hint
- Bottom-center: `[E] Interact` prompt (appears only near interactable objects)
- Bottom-right: Camera mode indicator (1st / 3rd person) + `[C]` hint
- No health bars, no survival meters — clean and friendly

### Pause Menu (ESC)
- Resume
- View Leaderboards
- Return to Main Menu
- Quit Game

---

## 9. Visual Art Style

| Element | Style |
|---------|-------|
| Color Palette | Vibrant purples, teals, golds, pinks — neon space carnival |
| Architecture | Rounded, bubble-shaped buildings with glowing trim |
| Ground | Smooth metallic/holographic floor tiles with glowing grid lines |
| Sky (Day) | Deep blue-purple space sky with a bright star/sun |
| Sky (Night) | Deep black with thousands of stars and nebula colors |
| Characters | Rounded, slightly cartoonish proportions |
| Lighting | Warm park lights + cool space ambient light |
| Effects | Particle sparkles, glowing halos around mini game stations |

