## 10. Technical Architecture

```
space_park/
│
├── main.py                  # Entry point, Ursina app init
├── scores.json              # Local high score storage
│
├── scenes/
│   ├── main_menu.py         # Character select + menu
│   ├── park.py              # Open world park scene
│   └── pause_menu.py        # Pause overlay
│
├── zones/
│   ├── entry_plaza.py       # Entry zone entities
│   ├── galaxy_games.py      # Games zone layout
│   └── cosmic_rides.py      # Rides zone layout
│
├── minigames/
│   ├── asteroid_shooting.py
│   ├── whack_a_mole.py
│   ├── space_maze.py
│   └── rocket_race.py
│
├── player/
│   ├── player.py            # Player entity, movement, camera
│   └── camera_controller.py # Smooth camera logic
│
├── systems/
│   ├── day_night.py         # Day/night toggle system
│   ├── score_manager.py     # Load/save scores.json
│   └── npc_manager.py       # Alien NPC ambient movement
│
└── assets/
    ├── models/              # 3D models (.obj or Ursina built-ins)
    ├── textures/            # Texture images
    └── fonts/               # Custom space-style fonts
```

---

## 11. Installation & Setup

```bash
# Step 1: Install Ursina
pip install ursina

# Step 2: Run the game
python main.py
```

No additional setup required. All dependencies bundled via pip.

---

## 12. Development Phases

| Phase | Tasks | Priority |
|-------|-------|----------|
| **Phase 1** | Main menu, character select, basic park world, player movement, camera toggle | 🔴 Must |
| **Phase 2** | All 3 zones built, day/night cycle, NPCs, signage | 🔴 Must |
| **Phase 3** | All 4 mini games with scoring | 🔴 Must |
| **Phase 4** | Local leaderboard system, score screens | 🟡 High |
| **Phase 5** | Decorative rides animations, particle effects, polish | 🟢 Nice |

---

## 13. Constraints & Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **No background music** (per user requirement)
> - **No survival mechanics** — no health, oxygen, reactor, or mission timers
> - **No multiplayer** — single player only
> - All code written in **Python** using **Ursina Engine**
> - Camera must feel **smooth** — no snappy or rigorous movement
> - Day/Night toggled by **`N` key**, not automatic timer

---

